<p class="">The Chancellor never said that he was going to maintain subsidies at £425 million per annum beyond the period when the new cost-of-living index comes into operation. In fact, he hinted strongly that he hoped for a reduction.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
